criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Age: 18-85 years old;

          2. The peripheral pulmonary nodules found in patients with chest CT, preoperative
             examination showed that the clinical stage of patients was T1N0M0, IA;

          3. patients are not suitable for surgical treatment through multidisciplinary assessment,
             agree to accept ablation

          4. Patients have good compliance with the tests and follow-ups, understand the situation
             of the study and sign informed consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. The patient is generally in poor condition and cannot tolerate the examination;

          2. patients with a cardiac pacemaker or stent in the heart; peripheral tumors of the
             lungs are adjacent to large blood vessels or important structures;

          3. patients with poor compliance;

          4. Researchers believe that it is not appropriate to participate in this trial.
